Description: Washburn SB-8 with hard case. The SB-8 is one of Washburn’s Wing Series. The Wing Series included the SB-8, T- bird, Raven, Falcon, Hawk and Eagle.The SB-8 has the standard no nonsense fixed bridge with brass saddles. It has two volume knobs, one for each pickup and a tone knob. The neck pickup splits into a single coil with the push/ pull volume knob for that pickup.The SB-8 has a bolt on neck like a Stratocaster. The advantage of a bolt on neck over set or through necks is that there’s more neck adjustment possible for fine tuning of the setup if that is needed at any time. So there’s that, and if you ever need to replace parts, a bolt on neck can easily be replaced.The guitar is in very good condition. There are some scratches and several small indentations or chips in the finish. See photos for the best description.It plays and sounds great with low action and the frets show slight wear. There are no dead spots anywhere up the neck.All electronics work as they should and it sounds great plugged in. The serial number is not altered.
